<div class="commentary">
    <h3>Commentary</h3>
    <p>
        Jacques Bramson was head of the ORT school in Paris when interviewed by David Boder on August 16, 1946. He was the nephew of Leonty Moiseivich Bramson, a president of ORT. Born in Russia in 1911, Jacques Bramson and his family moved to Poland after the 1917 Russian revolution and then emigrated to France ...
        <a href="commentary?doc=bramsonJ&name=Jacques+Bramson+">
            Read full commentary &raquo;
        </a>
    </p>
</div>
